Jesus ALCAZAR, Plaintiff, and Cesar Rosas, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. The CORPORATION OF the CATHOLIC ARCHBISHOP OF SEATTLE; Horatio Yanez, Defendants-Appellees. No. 09-35003. United States Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Aug. 5, 2010. Lindsay L. Halm, Schroeter, Goldmark, & Bender, Seattle, WA, for Plaintiff-Appellant. Kathryn Goater, Rebecca J. Roe, Schroeter Goldmark & Bender, Seattle, WA, John J. Polito, Esquire, Richard B. Kilpatrick, P.S., Bellevue, WA, for Plaintiff-Appellant. Karen A. Kalzer, Patterson Buchanan Fobes Leitch & Kalzer, Inc., P.S., Michael A. Patterson, Patterson Law, Jack Michael Lovejoy, Mary Colleen Kinerk, Cable Langenback Kinerk & Bauer, Seattle, WA, for Defendants-Appellees.

D.C. No. 2:06-cv-00281-RSM.

*1102ORDER

KOZINSKI, Chief Judge:

Upon the vote of a majority of nonrecused active judges, it is ordered that this case be reheard en banc pursuant to Circuit Rule 35-8. The three-judge panel opinion shall not be cited as precedent by or to any court of the Ninth Circuit.
